A high-speed police chase in which a 13-year-old girl died began when a car triggered an automatic system designed to catch wanted criminals.

The teenager suffered catastrophic injuries and died at the scene when a car smashed into the back of her family’s VW Polo.

Her mother, father and four-year-old brother, who was sitting beside her in the back seat, were also injured in the crash in New Cross, South-East London.

