The computerised system is able to 
cross-reference number plates with police databases for wanted suspects,
uninsured drivers and stolen vehicles.

Last year the Met said it would double
the number of such cameras in London to make it more difficult for 
criminals to move around.

The accident took place outside a primary school and close to Millwall’s football ground shortly before 6.30pm on Sunday.

The Peugeot was chased from nearby Peckham by a marked police car with its sirens on and blue lights flashing.

