Witnesses said it collided with the rear of the Polo at a junction in a 30mph zone, shunting it into a wall.

The Peugeot was not stolen, A woman passenger suffered minor injuries and a man was arrested at the scene.

The Metropolitan Police said the girl’s father remained in hospital last night. Her mother and brother have been discharged.

Commander Tony Eastaugh said: ‘An innocent family are now dealing with the tragic loss of a loved one.’

